cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with memory optimization of deep neural networks for image classification and semantic segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach to reduce memory footprint without compromising computational efficiency, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of backward pass computations, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper reports state-of-the-art results on semantic segmentation tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
